This paper deals with user-cell association in wireless small cell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses matching theory with externalities to solve the problem, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the quality of service (QoS) requirements of users, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents simulation results that involve measuring the performance of the proposed approach, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
